      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Ah, the overlapping issue is a common problem, especially when dealing with the small screen size. It's like a mischievous little goblin playing hide and seek with your text. You might want to try adjusting the `margin-top` of the `.product-title` to give it a bit more space from the image. Sometimes, even a tiny bit of extra room can make a big difference. Also, consider using a media query to specifically target mobile devices and tweak the styles accordingly. Here's an example:\n\n```css\n@media (max-width: 600px) {\n  .product-title {\n    margin-top: 20px; /* Adjust this value as needed */\n  }\n}\n```\n\nThis should help your product title stand out and avoid the goblin's mischievous antics. Good luck!",
      "source": "target",
