      "content": "Ah, it seems like the layout is being stubborn, much like a goblin refusing to leave its hiding spot. Let's try another approach. Sometimes, the issue might not be with the margin itself, but with the container's width or the way the elements are positioned. Let's give it a try with a different layout method, like using `display: block` for the product title and adjusting the width of the product image to be a percentage of the container's width. This might help in giving the elements the space they crave:\n\n```css\n@media (max-width: 600px) {\n  .product-image {\n    width: 100%;\n    height: auto;\n  }\n\n  .product-title {\n    display: block;\n    width: 100%;\n    margin-top: 20px; /* Adjust this value as needed */\n  }\n}\n```\n\nThis change should help in giving your product title the space it needs to avoid the goblin's mischievous overlap. Remember, sometimes it's all about finding the right combination of spells (or styles) to make everything work together harmoniously. Good luck!",
